@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@
+# Solution
+
+`get()` returned live values without moving their keys to the end of the `OrderedDict`, so reads did not refresh recency and a recently accessed entry could be evicted. It now marks every successful lookup as most recently used.
+
+`put()` evicted an entry whenever the cache was full, even when the key already existed. It now evicts only when inserting a new key at capacity, allowing updates to replace the value and refresh recency without removing another entry.
